# RDS vs. Aurora

Choice = **engine · performance ceiling · workload variability**.

## Pick RDS when…

- **Oracle / SQL Server / Db2** — not on Aurora's list
- **MySQL/PG, cost-sensitive, predictable**, OK with 60–120 s failover

## Pick Aurora when…

- **MySQL/PG** + want **faster failover / replication**, up to **15 replicas**
- **Serverless v2** — variable / SaaS / dev-test / unknown scale
- **Global Database** — cross-region DR (RPO < 1 s), global reads
- **Backtrack** — guard against accidental wipes

## Cost shape

Aurora = per-sec compute + per-GB storage + per-IO. RDS = per-sec + **pre-provisioned EBS**. Small steady → RDS often cheaper; **bursty / growing → Aurora**.
